TerreStar Picks Dish to Open Bidding
TerreStar Networks Inc. selected Dish Network Corp. as the opening bidder in a looming bankruptcy-court auction after receiving a $1.375 billion offer for the mobile-communications business, according to court papers filed early Wednesday.
Dish, run by satellite mogul Charlie Ergen, will get a $27.5 million breakup fee should TerreStar sell itself to another suitor, according to court papers outlining details of the bid. Other suitors must top the offer by at least $55.5 million to outbid Dishâ€”a sum of Dish's breakup fee and...